data.name: Mushroom and Wild Rice Stuffing
data.quickTastyDescription: A hearty and flavorful stuffing made with earthy mushrooms and nutty wild rice, perfect for any occasion!
detailedCookingInstructions: In a saucepan, bring vegetable broth to a boil and add wild rice. Reduce heat, cover, and simmer for about 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat. Add chopped onion, celery, and garlic, saut√©ing until soft (about 5 minutes).
Add sliced mushrooms and thyme, cooking until mushrooms are tender and moisture is evaporated (about 5-7 minutes).
Combine the cooked wild rice with the mushroom mixture. Season with salt and pepper to taste, mixing well.
Serve warm as a side dish or stuffing.
data.detailedName: Hearty Mushroom and Wild Rice Stuffing
